cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the use of Inter-Vehicle Communications (IVC) for routing EVs around mobile charging stations, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method for routing EVs based on constraint logic programming and optimization using a graph-based shortest path algorithm, which involves the use of AI techniques. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of EVs and the charging infrastructure, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with the routing of EVs, which can be seen as a robotic task. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a computational method for optimizing the routing of EVs, which falls under the domain of computational engineering.
